types of backup we use in postgresql and restore of backups types and methods and with include options.....
1. Logical Backup
--> Plain SQL Backup
--> Custom Formate Backup
--> Directory Formate Backup
--> Tar Formate Backup

2. Physical Backup
--> File System Backup
--> Base Backup

3. Full backup --> entire database (can be logical or physical)

4. Incremental Backup --> Backup only changes since last backup

5. Differential Backup --> Backup changes since last full backup

6. Continuous Archiving(WAL backup) --> Uses Write-Ahead Log(WAL) files, and Helps in Point-In-Time Recovery (PITR)

7. Point-In-Time Recovery (PITR) / continous backup --> Restore database to a specific time 
   combination of Base backup and WAL archiving.

8. Snapshot Backup --> Uses storage-level snapshots like LVM.

9. Hot Backup --> backup taken while database is running

10. cold Backup --> Backup taken when database is stopped
